        Production Lead      


 
CHEVOO Inc 
in


Healdsburg, CA 95448





Production Lead


Healdsburg, California






Benefits Offered

                Vision, Medical
              


Employment Type




SummaryWe are looking for a high energy Production Lead to take on this key role in operating a high quality, state of the art operation. The Production Lead will be responsible for assisting the Operations Manager and Production Supervisor in undertaking all work assignments, including production and sanitation activities, to achieve on time delivery to customers. Tasks will including set up, production and sanitation duties to ensure that product is efficiently produced while maintaining food safety, food quality and employee safety standards.Essential Duties and Responsibilities Specifically, the responsibilities of the position include, but are not limited to, the following activities:· Perform all production line activities· Record all production line activities in accordance with SOPs and Work Instructions.· Perform all duties in compliance with FDA, USDA, OSHA and state and local regulations and company policies and procedures; including safety guidelines and the use of Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP's)· Sanitize all equipment used in the production plant ensuring all food safety standards have been met· Ensure equipment is maintained, sanitized and operating efficiently to produce a high quality and safe product· Assist training new employees on all food safety, production and sanitation activities· Review safety standards with team members and monitor employee safety compliance ensuring compliance with the necessary rules and regulations· Inspire passion and commitment. Build team morale to drive productivity and quality standards· Perform other duties as assigned by Operations Manager and Production SupervisorEducation · High school diploma or equivalent preferred· Dairy or food plant experience preferred· Ability to perform basic arithmetic and numeric calculationsComputer· Proficiency in Excel, Word and Outlook required· Experience with mobile ERP software highly desired Required Attributes· Must have reliable means of transportation to and from work· Commitment to excellence and high quality standards· Must be a cultural fit and have strong interpersonal skills· Ability to work quickly and efficiently in a fast-paced environment· Ability to lead people of different experiences and educational backgrounds· Technically oriented, comfortable around machinery and in food preparation environment· Must have a working knowledge of HACCP (HARPC) and GMPs· Ability to understand and follow written and verbal instructions· Creative, flexible, and innovative team player· Willingness to work within constantly changing priorities with enthusiasmCommunication · Effective communication skills in both verbal and written formatsLanguage Skills · Must be able to speak, read, write, and understand the primary language(s) used in the workplace· Bilingual is preferredCertificates, Licenses, Registrations · HACCP or Food Quality certified preferred· Forklift Safety certified preferredPhysical Requirements· Stand and walk for extended periods of time.· Ability to push/pull more than 1,000 pounds using a pallet jack· Ability to lift at least (50) pounds independently; bending; squatting; stooping; kneeling; climbing; or reaching for extended periods of time If you want to be a part of a small, energetic team, and be a part of building something special from the ground-up, then this job is for you!


About CHEVOO Inc:
All details about CHEVOO can be found at www.chevoo.com



