From the beginning, strict attention to every manufacturing detail has been the mantra at Chevoo.




Related Stories













	12 notable North Bay makers and manufacturers in 2017









“Our ability to ramp up so fast may appear unusual for a young company, but we wanted to invest in our future upfront to stay ahead of the growth curve,” Tuck said. “We looked ahead five years in an attempt to determine what we would need for production, space, equipment and team members so we could expand quickly and easily. Instead of just cobbling equipment together in an old random facility, we wanted to have everything in place to take advantage of future possibilities.”Anticipating a major step up in U.S. Department of Agriculture food regulations in 2018, Chevoo’s owners wanted to make sure they will comply.“As part of its ongoing vision for continuous improvement, the USDA wants to standardize and elevate food safety processes among the 10s of thousands of food manufacturers in the U.S., especially when it comes to the best ways to produce food,” Tuck said. “This is why we built an advanced manufacturing facility with quality assurance features that anticipate potential regulatory changes — and then some.”













































 





























































































